<h3>
	Juvenile records in Cook County (including Chicago): Contact the <a href="https://www.facebook.com/JuvenileExpungementHelpDesk">Juvenile Expungement Help Desk</a> at (312) 229-6359 and a lawyer will be able to help you.
</h3>

<br>
<h3>To get information about an arrest in Chicago (date, age, juvenile vs. adult), you can get your arrest record (aka rap sheet) at:</h3>
<p>
Records and Services Division of the Chicago Police Department<br>
3510 S Michigan, Chicago IL 60653<br>
(312)745-5508<br>
Mon-Fri 8am-3pm</p>
<br>


<br>

